handNote.desc:
The script is of small size;  
ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached to the body of the letter by means of the linking line; 
the upper part of some letters, e.g. ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ, has a triangular shape; 
መ and ዐ have angular loops; 
numerals are written without dashes; 
the crux ansata and the zǝya-sign are often used, the latter every 9 or 12 stichi in the left margin of the leaf (cp. 


    329
 ).

